Text:
How am I, I'm good thanks, how about you? My name is Phillip, but you can call me Phil. My full name is Philip Sparks.

 How old am I, I'm getting on a bit now, in my mid-40s. How old am I, I was born on the 3rd September 1980.

How old am I, I'm getting on a bit now, in my mid-40s. How old am I, I was born on the 3rd September 1980.

 Reason for visit. The reason I have come for a sight test today, what brings me along, why I am here today is because I can't read so well any more particularly if the lighting is poor. I'm not saying I can't read, I'm saying that it's blurry.

The reason I have come for a sight test today, what brings me along, why I am here today is because I can't read so well any more particularly if the lighting is poor. I'm not saying I can't read, I'm saying that it's blurry. It's been blurry for about six months or so. It's not so bad if the light is good but when the lighting is poor I really struggle. Restaurants are a pain for this, why are the lights so dim in there, I struggle to read menus when the lighting isn't so good.

It's not so bad if the light is good but when the lighting is poor I really struggle. Restaurants are a pain for this, why are the lights so dim in there, I struggle to read menus when the lighting isn't so good.

 My last eye examination, to be honest I really can't remember it must have been ages ago. I guess my last eye examination might have been about 10 years ago. I'm hopeless at getting my eyes tested.

I guess my last eye examination might have been about 10 years ago. I'm hopeless at getting my eyes tested. I don't have any glasses. I have never had any glasses. I don't have any contact lenses either, do you like contact lenses?

Other symptoms.

I have never had any glasses. I don't have any contact lenses either, do you like contact lenses?

Other symptoms. I don't really get headaches normally, but lately if I'm trying to read something small or in dim light I get a bit of headache. The headache is just a general one, not in any particular part of my head. My distance vision is fine, I can see what I need to and sometimes more than I need to.

The headache is just a general one, not in any particular part of my head. My distance vision is fine, I can see what I need to and sometimes more than I need to. I don't get flashes of light in my vision. I don't get floating bits in my vision. I don't get double vision unless I've had a few too many, sometimes I drink too much get a bit tipsy

I don't get floating bits in my vision. I don't get double vision unless I've had a few too many, sometimes I drink too much get a bit tipsy and then I can get some double vision, but I think that's normal. I don't normally get double vision. I don't have dry eyes or itchy eyes.

I don't normally get double vision. I don't have dry eyes or itchy eyes.

 My ocular history and previous eye problems. I did have to go to the hospital for my eye a few years ago, back when I was an apprentice in the early 2000s. I was cutting a high-tension wire and a small strand broke off and hit me right in the eye.

I did have to go to the hospital for my eye a few years ago, back when I was an apprentice in the early 2000s. I was cutting a high-tension wire and a small strand broke off and hit me right in the eye. It was really painful! I went to the hospital who said that it would sort itself out, and it has. At the hospital they didn't give me any eye drops or anything, they just sent me home.

I went to the hospital who said that it would sort itself out, and it has. At the hospital they didn't give me any eye drops or anything, they just sent me home. I never had an eye patched as a child.

 Family ocular and medical history. Everyone in my family is fine, they don't seem to have anything wrong with their eyes.

Family ocular and medical history. Everyone in my family is fine, they don't seem to have anything wrong with their eyes. As far as I know my family don't have any eye problems but, some of them wear glasses for reading, but that's it. Mum had a heart attack a few years ago, but there's nothing else in the family. I don't think there's diabetes in the family.

Mum had a heart attack a few years ago, but there's nothing else in the family. I don't think there's diabetes in the family. There might be high blood pressure; mum had a heart attack after all! 

 My general health. General health is fine, I've a dodgy back from years in industry

My general health. General health is fine, I've a dodgy back from years in industry so I take painkillers if it plays me up. I don't take painkillers very often just when my back is playing up. Smoking, are you kidding me!
I don't take painkillers very often just when my back is playing up. Smoking, are you kidding me! I hate smoking, awful. I have never smoked. I don't have any allergies.

I have never smoked. I don't have any allergies.

 My medication. Sometimes I take painkillers for my dodgy back but that's it.

Sometimes I take painkillers for my dodgy back but that's it. I'm not on any prescription medication.

 My occupation and hobbies. I'm an electrician.

My occupation and hobbies. I'm an electrician. Started out on the National Grid but I've come off those contracts now and just do domestic. It's much easier and means that I can work for myself. I'm a big fan of 70s music, and in particular ELO.
It's much easier and means that I can work for myself. I'm a big fan of 70s music, and in particular ELO. Have you heard of them? They did Mr. Blue Sky. Don't ask me to sing it though!

They did Mr. Blue Sky. Don't ask me to sing it though! I really enjoy listening to music.

 Computer use and driving. I try to avoid computers.

Computer use and driving. I try to avoid computers. I guess I spend about an hour a day looking at the screen but only really only when I have to, like when I have to sort out the invoices for customers. I drive a car but don't need or use any glasses for that.


 I don't think there's anything else to say.
